The ATO Dictionary

Source: vignettes/articles/ato-dictionary.qmd

Find the Google Sheets version here.

slots

slot defining class other classes optional classes
@det ATO_det data.frame data.table, tibble
@dep ATO_dep data.frame data.table, tibble
@tag ATO_tag data.frame data.table, tibble
@ani ATO_ani data.frame data.table, tibble
@obs ATO_obs data.frame data.table, tibble
@log ATO_log data.frame data.table, tibble
@tbl ATO_tbl character -

columns

slot (3 letters) column name (snake case) column type auto or manual short description
@det (detections) datetime POSIXct manual date and time of the detection (yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss)
@det (detections) frac_second numeric manual fraction of the second when the detection was received
@det (detections) receiver_serial integer manual serial number of the receiver that picked up the detection
@det (detections) transmitter character manual transmitter that was picked up
@det (detections) sensor_value numeric manual respective sensor value
@det (detections) … any manual non-standard column names are allowed
@det (detections) valid logical automatic Should this detection be used for analyses?
@det (detections) tag_match logical automatic created by either match_det_tag or match_det_dep, indicates if detection matches a target transmitter (either in the tag slot or the dep slot)
@det (detections) dep_match logical automatic created by match_det_tag, indicates if detection falls within a deployment period for a known receiver
@det (detections) animal character automatic created by match_det_ani, when the ATO has both det, tag, and ani. Technically only needs the det and tag slots
@dep (deployments) receiver_manufacturer character manual company that made the receiver
@dep (deployments) receiver_model character manual model of the receiver
@dep (deployments) receiver_serial integer manual serial code of the receiver (this is the column used to match deployments)
@dep (deployments) receiver_codeset character manual codeset of the receiver
@dep (deployments) transmitter character manual Can either be a beacon located inside a receiver, or a stationary reference transmitter
@dep (deployments) transmitter_manufacturer character manual company that made the transmitter
@dep (deployments) transmitter_ping_rate numeric manual ping rate of the transmitter
@dep (deployments) transmitter_model character manual model of the transmitter
@dep (deployments) transmitter_serial integer manual serial code of the transmitter
@dep (deployments) deploy_location character manual name of the location where the receiver was deployed
@dep (deployments) deploy_datetime POSIXct manual date and time of the deployment (yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss)
@dep (deployments) deploy_lat numeric manual latitude of the deployment
@dep (deployments) deploy_lon numeric manual longitude of the deployment
@dep (deployments) deploy_z numeric manual depth of the deployment (as measured from the reference surface of the waterbody)
@dep (deployments) recover_datetime POSIXct manual date and time of the recovery (yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss)
@dep (deployments) recover_lat numeric manual latitude of the recovery
@dep (deployments) recover_lon numeric manual longitude of the recovery
@dep (deployments) … any manual non-standard column names are allowed
@dep (deployments) n_detections numeric automatic created by match_det_dep. number of detections recorded during the deployment
@tag manufacturer character manual company that made the tag
@tag model character manual model of the tag
@tag power_level numeric manual power level of the tag
@tag ping_rate numeric manual ping rate of the tag
@tag ping_variation numeric manual +- variation added to individual pings
@tag serial integer manual serial code of the tag
@tag transmitter character manual transmitter code emitted by the tag
@tag activation_datetime POSIXct manual activation date
@tag battery_life numeric manual battery life
@tag sensor_type character manual sensor type associated with the transmitter (e.g. temperature)
@tag sensor_unit character manual units of the sensor data collected (e.g. C)
@tag animal character manual name/code of the animal that received the tag
@tag … any manual non-standard column names are allowed
@tag det_match logical automatic created by match_det_tag, indicates if the transmitter was ever detected
@tag obs_match logical automatic created by match_obs_tag, indicates if the transmitter was ever observed
@tag ani_match logical automatic created by match_tag_ani. Indicates if the value in @tag$animal matches a value in @ani$animal
@ani (animal) animal character manual name/code of the animal
@ani (animal) capture_location character manual place where the animal was caught
@ani (animal) capture_datetime POSIXct manual date and time when the animal was caught
@ani (animal) capture_lat numeric manual latitude of the capture
@ani (animal) capture_lon numeric manual longitude of the capture
@ani (animal) release_location character manual place where the animal was released
@ani (animal) release_datetime POSIXct manual date and time when the animal was released
@ani (animal) release_lat numeric manual latitude of the release
@ani (animal) release_lon numeric manual longitude of the release
@ani (animal) … any manual non-standard column names are allowed
@ani (animal) det_match logical automatic created by match_det_ani, indicates if the animal was ever detected
@ani (animal) obs_match logical automatic created by match_obs_ani. indicates if the anmal was ever observed
@ani (animal) tag_match logical automatic created by match_tag_ani. Indicates if the animal has associated transmitters
@obs (observations) animal character manual name/code of the observed animal
@obs (observations) transmitter character manual transmitter detected
@obs (observations) type character manual type of observation (e.g. manual tracking, visual, etc)
@obs (observations) terminal logical manual does this observation mark the end of tracking for this animal
@obs (observations) location character manual location of the observation
@obs (observations) datetime POSIXct manual date and time of the observation
@obs (observations) lat numeric manual latitude of the observation
@obs (observations) lon numeric manual longitude of the observation
@obs (observations) … any manual non-standard column names are allowed
@obs (observations) valid logical automatic Should this observation be used for analyses?
@obs (observations) tag_match logical automatic created by match_obs_tag. indicates if the observation matches a transmitter in the tag slot
@obs (observations) ani_match logical automatic created by match_obs_ani. indicates if the observation matches an animal in the ani slot
@log (internal log) datetime POSIXct automatic date and time of the entry
@log (internal log) type character automatic the type of event
@log (internal log) pkg character automatic package to which the funciton belongs
@log (internal log) fun character automatic function that wrote the entry
@log (internal log) call character automatic the full function call
@log (internal log) log character automatic summary of the changes introduced by the function
@tbl (character string) character automatic Type of tables used in the ATO (data.frame, data.table, or tibble)

methods

method package method family method name method signature arguments description
ATO add add ATO, ATO_det x, value assign “value” to the @det slot of the ATO
ATO add add ATO, ATO_dep x, value assign “value” to the @dep slot of the ATO
ATO add add ATO, ATO_tag x, value assign “value” to the @tag slot of the ATO
ATO add add ATO, ATO_ani x, value assign “value” to the @ani slot of the ATO
ATO add add ATO, ATO_obs x, value assign “value” to the @obs slot of the ATO
ATO get_ get_det ATO x, receivers, transmitters extract the @det slot from the ATO. arguments allow refining which detections are extracted.
ATO get_ get_det_dep ATO x, receivers wrapper to extract the @det slot from the ATO and filter only the transmitters listed in @det
ATO get_ get_det_tag ATO x, receivers wrapper to extract the @det slot from the ATO and filter only the transmitters listed in the @tag
ATO get_ get_dep ATO x extract the @dep slot from the ATO
ATO get_ det_tag ATO x extract the @tag slot from the ATO
ATO get_ det_ani ATO x extract the @ani slot from the ATO
ATO get_ det_obs ATO x extract the @obs slot from the ATO

ATO summary summary ATO_dep object prints a summary of the dep slot
ATO summary summary ATO_tag object prints a summary of the tag slot
ATO summary summary ATO_ani object prints a summary of the ani slot
ATO summary summary ATO_obs object prints a summary of the obs slot
ATO summary summary ATO_log object prints a summary of the log slot
